<?xml-model ../out/tls1.rnc application/relax-ng-compact-syntax?><div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:mods="http://www.loc.gov/mods/v3" xmlns:tls="http://tls.kanripo.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" type="concept" xml:id="uuid-57af8b26-a912-4bd4-ad86-7e98a0673dc5"><head>CIRCLE</head><list type="altnames"><item>RING</item><item>BAND</item><item>HOOP</item><item>CIRCLET</item><item>HALO</item><item>DISC</item></list><list type="translations"><item xml:lang="zh">圈子 </item></list><div type="definition"><p>PERFECTLY ROUND FLAT SHAPE.</p></div><div type="notes"><div type="old-chinese-criteria"><p>1. The common general term for a circle is yuán 員 / 圓.</p><p>2. Zhōu 周 refers to an irregular circle shape; it is used for a length of perimeter of a circle.</p><p>3. Huán 環 refers to an irregular circle shape; it is used for an area surrounded by a circle.</p><p>4. Tuán 摶 is a word for a circle that was in use in a southern state of &gt;Chǔ 楚.</p><p>5. Guī 規 occasionally refers to a standard round shape, but the word is seldom used in this sense.</p></div><div type="modern-chinese-criteria"><p>圈子</p><p>圓圈</p><p>圈</p><p>周</p><p>匝</p><p>旋</p><p>環</p><p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p></div></div><div type="pointers"><list type="taxonymy"><item><ref target="#uuid-7c794d5a-d3f0-4ed1-a61b-363bb4bfa27f">SURROUND</ref></item></list><list type="see"><item><ref target="#uuid-362ff7ea-a564-430d-a3f0-a3b355fdd85a">RING</ref></item></list></div><div type="source-references"><listBibl><bibl><ref target="#uuid-60d39cc0-d76b-4275-8490-886ace4204be">BUCK 1988</ref><title>A Dictionary of Selected Synonyms in the Principal Indo-European Languages</title><biblScope unit="page">12.82</biblScope><note><p/></note></bibl><bibl><ref target="#uuid-ab831347-9626-498d-aa1e-eb43eae72d05">DOEDERLEIN 1840</ref><title>Lateinische Synonyme und Etymologien</title><note><p>CIRCLE</p><p>orbis refers to a circular motion, and the periphery described by it.</p><p>circulus refers to a circular level plain as such.</p><p>gyrus refers to a curved and especially a serpentine line.</p></note></bibl><bibl><ref target="#uuid-56dd8ede-a572-47bc-8a1b-70c846775874">MENGE</ref><title>Lateinische Synonymik</title><biblScope unit="page">261</biblScope><note><p/></note></bibl><bibl><ref target="#uuid-4acb4e0c-daab-4369-9991-912c64da1ee6">RITTER 1971-2007</ref><title>Historisches Woerterbuch der Philosophie</title><biblScope unit="page">4.1211</biblScope><note><p/></note></bibl><bibl><ref target="#uuid-3cf76dec-e8bc-4732-bde9-e5ca60e7fb1a">SCHMIDT 1889</ref><title>Handbuch der lateinischen und griechischen Synonymik</title><biblScope unit="page">103</biblScope><note><p/></note></bibl><bibl><ref target="#uuid-65cb3fa8-ba3e-4eef-b23e-5b43a8bb8651">JONES 2005</ref><title>Encyclopedia of Religion</title><note><p/></note></bibl></listBibl></div><div type="words"><entry type="word" xml:id="uuid-1a1537be-eb02-4e0c-a9e6-8868c053b5b7"><form corresp="#uuid-6f54daf0-aa06-4469-8d5c-52be1bac8d50"><orth>周</orth><pron xml:lang="zh-Latn-x-pinyin">zhōu</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-oc">tjɯw</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-mc">tɕɨu</pron><listBibl><bibl><ref target="#uuid-71cc6340-5a8f-41ae-83b2-178447c6895a">DUAN DESEN 1992A</ref><title>簡明古漢語同義詞詞典</title><biblScope unit="page">957</biblScope><note><p/></note></bibl><bibl><ref target="#uuid-71cc6340-5a8f-41ae-83b2-178447c6895a">DUAN DESEN 1992A</ref><title>簡明古漢語同義詞詞典</title><biblScope unit="page">957</biblScope><note><p/></note></bibl></listBibl></form><sense xml:id="uuid-f63e48a1-fc7d-4efd-af6d-8b2f3dbde7b5"><gramGrp><pos>N</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-76be1df4-3d73-4e5f-bbc2-729542645bc8">nab</tls:syn-func><tls:sem-feat corresp="#uuid-b110bae1-02d5-4c66-ad13-7c04b3ee3ad9">mathematical term</tls:sem-feat></gramGrp><def>CHEMLA 2003: circumference of a circle. By extension the term may refer to the circumferences of an annulus/ring or circular tube or a segment of sphere. LIU HUI 1.32 故以半周乘半徑而為圓冪 "Therefore with the half of the circumference one multiplies half of the diameter and thus arrives at the area of the circle." (There are plenty of earlier examples.)JIUZHANG 1.33 今有宛田，下周三十步，徑十六步。 "Suppose there is an yuan4 (i.e. segment-of-the-sphere) "field" pattern, its lower circumference is 30 paces, and its diameter is 16 paces."JZ 1.32, Li Chunfeng's comm: 是二六相乘，除周自乘之數 "Thus the product of two and six divides the quantity of the square of the circumference."JIUZHANG 1.37 今有環田，中周九十二步，外周一百二十二步，徑五步。 "Suppose there is a "field" pattern in the shape of a ring, and its inner circumference is 92 paces, its outer circumference is 122 paces, and its diameter is five paces." (NB: The outer circumference is at the outside of the ring, and the inner circumference is at the inside of the ring.)</def></sense><sense xml:id="uuid-2b100a26-056d-4faa-801b-b65fe6c31880"><gramGrp><pos>V</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-2a0ded86-3b04-4488-bb7a-3efccfa35844">vadV</tls:syn-func></gramGrp><def>in circles; circulating</def></sense></entry><entry type="word" xml:id="uuid-ceea249f-d96f-40d0-85e9-c50a242b35e3"><form corresp="#uuid-096738fe-9bfc-4d8f-9b61-7e6f84e3076a"><orth>員</orth><pron xml:lang="zh-Latn-x-pinyin">yuán</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-oc">ɢon</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-mc">ɦiɛn</pron></form><form corresp="#uuid-330e25a2-1611-4048-b2cb-ec2e25ca905b"><orth>圓</orth><pron xml:lang="zh-Latn-x-pinyin">yuán</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-oc">ɢon</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-mc">ɦiɛn</pron></form><sense xml:id="uuid-22252b1e-c069-441d-87c7-822004fe8bf3"><gramGrp><pos>N</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-8717712d-14a4-4ae2-be7a-6e18e61d929b">n</tls:syn-func></gramGrp><def>circle</def></sense></entry><entry type="word" xml:id="uuid-32b922d6-b37d-453f-b3d5-56bcaa5f91a9"><form corresp="#uuid-330e25a2-1611-4048-b2cb-ec2e25ca905b"><orth>圓</orth><pron xml:lang="zh-Latn-x-pinyin">yuán</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-oc">ɢon</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-mc">ɦiɛn</pron></form><sense xml:id="uuid-d635d2ef-6f59-4bf0-9063-e5c18b7505d3"><gramGrp><pos>N</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-8717712d-14a4-4ae2-be7a-6e18e61d929b">n</tls:syn-func><tls:sem-feat corresp="#uuid-50da9f38-5611-463e-a0b9-5bbb7bf5e56f">subject</tls:sem-feat><usg type="warring-states-currency">4</usg></gramGrp><def>a circle; something round</def></sense><sense xml:id="uuid-60895a14-1e91-4b10-ae76-dce1b1f1a539"><gramGrp><pos>N</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-76be1df4-3d73-4e5f-bbc2-729542645bc8">nab</tls:syn-func><tls:sem-feat corresp="#uuid-b110bae1-02d5-4c66-ad13-7c04b3ee3ad9">mathematical term</tls:sem-feat></gramGrp><def>CHEMLA 2003: circle; particularly surface of a circle or in technical mathematical terminology "disk".LIU HUI 1.32 故以半周乘半徑而為圓冪 "Therefore with the half of the circumference one multiplies half of the diameter and thus arrives at the area of the circle."</def></sense></entry><entry type="word" xml:id="uuid-9280206f-2be1-4875-9961-b4492223fece"><form corresp="#uuid-514f63fa-9d09-4c30-b321-4e75042656d7"><orth>摶</orth><pron xml:lang="zh-Latn-x-pinyin">tuán</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-oc">doon</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-mc">dʷɑn</pron></form><sense xml:id="uuid-9140c6ad-2f2f-407a-b0e5-e8aa095805d0"><gramGrp><pos>V</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-c20780b3-41f9-491b-bb61-a269c1c4b48f">vi</tls:syn-func></gramGrp><def>circulate; move in circles</def></sense><sense xml:id="uuid-12d154de-6403-4241-9886-2e61b3dace9f"><gramGrp><pos>V</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-fbfb2371-2537-4a99-a876-41b15ec2463c">vtoN</tls:syn-func><tls:sem-feat corresp="#uuid-fac754df-5669-4052-9dda-6244f229371f">causative</tls:sem-feat><usg type="warring-states-currency">1</usg></gramGrp><def>cause to be round&gt; to roll into a ball</def></sense></entry><entry type="word" xml:id="uuid-ade3635b-fae7-4c6c-b7ed-f2e8c3876dfb"><form corresp="#uuid-d934eae9-08b0-4bcc-8323-0fded6425a9c"><orth>環</orth><pron xml:lang="zh-Latn-x-pinyin">huán</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-oc">ɡʷraan</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-mc">ɦɣan</pron></form><sense xml:id="uuid-8368adab-0864-4477-bb42-052037548709"><gramGrp><pos>N</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-8717712d-14a4-4ae2-be7a-6e18e61d929b">n</tls:syn-func></gramGrp><def>circle; ring; center of circle</def></sense></entry><entry type="word" xml:id="uuid-06f5ccda-87aa-4320-81ed-c79cc8a93f02"><form corresp="#uuid-aeae44dd-32f9-4c1c-8720-12903bd2d330"><orth>規</orth><pron xml:lang="zh-Latn-x-pinyin">guī</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-oc">kʷe</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-mc">kiɛ</pron></form></entry><entry type="word" xml:id="uuid-29bb135a-9601-44e5-a7c4-e3d62b5f5891"><form corresp="#uuid-a2da5941-cd61-4c93-ac0c-7f5955d5f526 #uuid-330e25a2-1611-4048-b2cb-ec2e25ca905b"><orth>團圓</orth><pron xml:lang="zh-Latn-x-pinyin">tuán yuán</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-oc">doon ɢon</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-mc">dʷɑn ɦiɛn</pron></form><sense xml:id="uuid-c52a6149-35f8-4918-8a2e-e6020e6712bc"><gramGrp><pos>N</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-a8e89bab-49e1-4426-b230-0ec7887fd8b4">NP</tls:syn-func></gramGrp><def>circle</def></sense></entry></div></div>